    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/graphic-communication/GCM/240.html" title="GCM 240 - Material Science for Print" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">GCM 240</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Material Science for Print</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course introduces students to the science of materials, including paper, ink, toners and other materials used in the printing industry. Tests are conducted for printability, runability and end-use properties. Students learn how to interpret observations and raw data, and through various testing protocols, learn how to meaningfully report results, and make evidence-based recommendations. Students learn how to collaborate with clients, designers and printers to select the best materials for a printing project.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 1 hr. Lab: 2 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
