    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/graphic-communication/GCM/710.html" title="GCM 710 - The Art of the Book" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">GCM 710</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">The Art of the Book</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">The book is credited with influencing culture and knowledge throughout the centuries. This course has two main focuses. It looks at how the book has evolved from before Gutenberg, to the time of Gutenberg about 600 hundred years ago, and to the present day book; as book art, ebook, graphica and ezines. The second focus looks at how print technology and electronic print technology has evolved along with the book. (Formerly GRA 510).</div>
	
	
