		<div class="courseListDescription">Existing printing technologies are regularly applied to non-traditional applications that go beyond output of visual materials. Non-traditional printing and coating applications include printed electronics, circuits, batteries and displays, visual indicators of thermal or chemical exposure, security, anti-counterfeiting and brand protection, and printing of textiles, foods and other irregular media. Characteristics and applications of various printing processes and materials are discussed.</div>
	
	
